{"editorCode":"        ;Vote for president\r\n\r\n\r\n;Tove made the procedure \"votes\" in order to construct a circular chart which shows the votes for each one of the 4 candidates for the election of the village president.  \r\n;200 village residents voted.\r\n;Candidate A took 40 votes, candidate B took an amount of votes that corresponds to the angle of 108 degrees of a cyclical sector of the chart; canditate C took 95 votes and candidate D the rest of them.\r\n;When Tove ran the procedure, she saw that the total amount of votes was not 200. How did she figure this out?\r\n\r\n;----------------        \r\n;----------------\r\n;For further instructions click on the papyrus button.\r\n;----------------        \r\n;----------------\r\n;Procedures\r\n;............\r\n\r\nto repres_data :r :y\r\nrt 90 fd :r \r\nlt (180-(:y/200)*200)\r\nprint (180-(:y/200)*200)\r\nfd :r\r\nrt 90\r\nend\r\n\r\nclean\r\nrepres_data 60 40 \r\n;--------------\r\n\r\nto votes :r \r\nstarting_point\r\nblack\r\ncircle :r\r\nblue\r\nrepres_data :r ... ;votes for A\r\ngreen\r\nrepres_data :r ... ;votes for B\r\nlight_blue\r\nrepres_data :r ... ;votes for C\r\nred\r\nrepres_data :r ... ;votes for D\r\nEND\r\n\r\n\r\nclean \r\nvotes 70\r\n;============\r\n\r\nTO circle :r\r\nrepeat 360 [rt 1 fd 2*pi*:r/360]\r\nend\r\n\r\nclean\r\n\r\n;---------\r\nto light_blue\r\nsetpencolor [30 144 255]\r\nEND\r\n\r\nto red\r\nsetpencolor [255 0 0]\r\nEND\r\n\r\nto black\r\nsetpencolor [0 0 0]\r\nend\r\n\r\nto blue\r\nsetpencolor [0 0 255]\r\nend\r\n\r\nto green\r\nsetpencolor [0 255 0]\r\nend\r\n\r\n\r\nTO starting_point\r\npu setpos [-70 0 0] pd\r\nEND\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n","hiddenCode":[],"sceneCode":"","cameraPos":{"x":0,"y":1.2246467991473532e-14,"z":200},"character":"Bird","notes":"                    VOTE FOR PRESIDENT\n\t\t***************************************************\n\nTASK 1\n................................\n1. Run the procedure \"repres_data\" and try to figure out what the avatar constructs. Explore the role of the variables :y, :r using the variation tool.\n\n 2. Complete the gaps \"...\" on the procedure \"votes\", before running it, with the right values that correspond to the amount of votes taken by each one of the 4 candidates. \n\n   •    What does the avatar construct on the circular chart?\n   •    Can you identify the problem?\n\n   Fix the procedure which is responsible for the problem.\n\nTASK 2\n.................................\n1. Generalize the procedure in order to compute the votes taken by a random number of voters (not only for 200 voters).\n\n\n\t\t\t\t----------------\n\t\t\t\t      TIPS\n\t\t\t\t----------------\n1. What is the connection between the votes that candidate C received and the angle of 108 degrees?\n  You can transform this piece of information in another (numerical) form.\n2.In order to identify the problem you can use the help of the procedure you used in order to transform your information.\n \n\n\n\n\n","sliders":{},"objects":[]}